article_title: Humana May Withdraw From Obamacare Exchanges

article_metadata.author: Bruce Japsen

og.description: Humana profits fell 30% in last year's fourth quarter with the insurer unable to manage the rising medical costs of newly insured Americans signing up for individual coverage under the Affordable Care Act, leaving its participation on public exchanges in doubt beyond this year.
